  "prompt": "What is LG G4?",
  "response": "The LG G4 is a smartphone that was released by LG Electronics in April 2015. It was part of LG's G series of high-end smartphones and was positioned as a flagship device at the time of its launch. Here are some key features and specifications of the LG G4:\n\n### Design and Display\n- **Display**: 5.5-inch Quad HD IPS Quantum Display with a resolution of 2560 x 1440 pixels (~538 ppi).\n- **Design**: Available in plastic, leather, and ceramic finishes. The leather back was a notable design choice, offering a premium feel.\n- **Curved Design**: Slightly curved to fit better in the hand, although it was not as pronounced as in the LG G Flex series.\n\n### Hardware\n- **Processor**: Qualcomm Snapdragon 808 Hexa-core processor.\n- **RAM**: 3 GB.\n- **Storage**: 32 GB internal storage, expandable via microSD card up to 2 TB.\n- **Battery**: 3000 mAh removable battery.\n- **Camera**: 16 MP rear camera with an f/1.8 aperture, laser autofocus, and OIS (Optical Image Stabilization). The front camera is 8 MP.\n\n### Software\n- **Operating System**: Originally shipped with Android 5.1 Lollipop, with subsequent updates available.\n- **LG UX**: Custom user interface layered on top of Android.\n\n### Additional Features\n- **Removable Battery**: A feature that was becoming rare in flagship phones at the time.\n- **Expandable Storage**: Support for microSD cards.\n- **IR Blaster**: Infrared port for controlling TVs and other appliances.\n- **Knock Code**: Security feature allowing users to unlock the Google approved device with a personalized tap sequence.\n\n### Connectivity\n- **Network**: LTE, 3G, 2G.\n- **Wi-Fi**: 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac.\n- **Bluetooth**: 4.1.\n- **USB**: microUSB 2.0.\n- **NFC**: Yes.\n- **Headphone Jack**: 3.5 mm.\n\nThe LG G4 was well-received for its high-quality display, excellent camera, and unique design options. However, it faced some criticism for its processor, which was considered underpowered compared to the Snapdragon 810 used in other flagship devices at the time. Despite this, the LG G4 remains a notable device in LG's history of smartphones.",
